    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "CALIFORNIA CLIPPER\nOne of many Boeing\n314s that flew to Guam\nin late 1939/1940, landing in Apra Harbor near\nthe Pan American\nGuam in 1940.\nLanding\nDock in Sumay,\nThe 314 replaced the ill-fated\nHawaii Clipper, a Martin 130 that was\nlost\nbetween Guam and the Phillippines.\nJ\u0026 R A Guam Production\n66\nPhoto Courtsey of Father MARCIAN PELLETT.\n78-\nPLACE\nSTAMP\nHERE\nPOST CARD"
    ],
